context:
Extracted Information:

1. Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) are used to measure the college's performance in meeting the needs of graduates and employers.
2. Graduates are surveyed six months and two years after graduation for the Graduate Satisfaction Survey.
3. Employers are surveyed to provide feedback on the preparedness of the hired graduate in the Employer Satisfaction Survey.
4. A third-party company tabulates the survey results, while George Brown manages, processes, and analyzes them.
5. Ontario Student Assistance Program (OSAP) default rates are part of the KPIs.
6. OSAP default rate calculations can be found on the gov.on.ca website.
7. Contact information for reaching out to George Brown College: 416-415-2000, TTY: 1-877-515-5559, ask.george@georgebrown.ca
8. Social media hub is available on the college's website.
9. The information contained in the website is subject to change without notice.
